{"task_id": "read_readme_summary", "task": "Use the read_file tool to read README.md, then summarize this project in 5 bullet points.", "status": "completed", "passed": true, "checks": {"status": true, "expected_tools": true, "forbidden_tools": true, "expected_text": true, "expected_any_text": true, "expected_observation": true}, "latency_seconds": 5.687237124890089, "tool_calls": [{"name": "read_file", "arguments": {"path": "README.md"}}], "usage": {"prompt_tokens": 9012, "completion_tokens": 392, "total_tokens": 9404, "prompt_tokens_details": {"cached_tokens": 512}, "completion_tokens_details": {"reasoning_tokens": 18}, "prompt_cache_hit_tokens": 768, "prompt_cache_miss_tokens": 8244}, "cost_usd": 0.00137144, "cost_breakdown_usd": {"prompt": 0.00126168, "completion": 0.00010976, "embedding": 0.0, "tool": 0.0, "total": 0.00137144}, "failure_category": "success", "final": "- **Lightweight LLM Agent Harness**: A locally runnable, model-agnostic framework for building and testing LLM agents with a built-in agent loop, tool registry, and provider adapters for multiple LLM APIs.\n- **Tool Registry**: Includes built-in tools: `list_dir`, `read_file`, `write_file`, and `run_shell`, with permission policies like read-only mode, shell allowlists, and dangerous command blocking.\n- **Evaluation & Determinism**: Comes with an evaluation benchmark that checks success rate, tool accuracy, latency, token usage, cost, and failure categories; also supports determinism checks by running the same task multiple times.\n- **Trace, Replay & Dashboard**: Every run produces a JSON transcript; you can render traces as Markdown with Mermaid flowcharts, replay runs for debugging, and generate a static HTML dashboard summarizing evaluations and runs.\n- **Local RAG & Extensibility**: Includes a local RAG index that works without an embedding API using lexical retrieval, and outlines planned extensions like a Web UI, concurrent task execution, and embedding-backed RAG.", "run_id": "20260629T151716Z-22452d1d", "error": null}
